r%20arsenal%20of%20Soviet-made%20fighter%20jets%2C%20asserting%20that%20the%20Western%20fighter%20jets%20will%20be%20critical%20assets%2C%20even%20if%20they%20won't%20necessarily%20be%20silver%20bullets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EF-16s%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20a%20massive%20improvement%20on%20what%20the%20Ukrainian%20fighter%20pilots%20are%20flying%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Justin%20Bronk%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Royal%20Norwegian%20Air%20Force%20Academy%20and%20senior%20research%20fellow%20for%20airpower%20and%20technology%20in%20the%20military%20sciences%20team%20at%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20told%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20US-made%20fourth-generation%20jets%20would%20come%20with%20a%20huge%20global%20supply%20chain%20and%20upgradeable%20features%20that%20Kyiv's%20current%20jets%20don't%20have.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finternational-pressure-biden-send-f-16-fighter-jets-ukraine-working-2023-5%5C%22%3Erecent%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20matter%20from%20the%20US%20and%20its%20NATO%20allies%2C%20it's%20possible%20that%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20could%20start%20training%20on%20the%20jets%20in%20August%20and%20that%20F-16s%20could%20be%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Ukraine%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20potentially%20helping%20challenge%20Russia's%20extensive%20air%20defense%20systems%20and%20providing%20support%20for%20ground%20operations%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there's%20no%20definitive%20timeline%20for%20when%20Ukraine%20might%20get%20the%20F-16s%20it%20has%20been%20asking%20for%2C%20their%20expected%20eventual%20delivery%20and%20employment%20in%20battle%20would%20likely%20be%20a%20boon%20for%20the%20Ukrainian%20air%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUkraine's%20current%20air%20force%20faces%20immense%20challenges%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ground%20staff%20directs%20Mig-29%20fighter%20jet%20of%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20after%20a%20flight%20a%20during%20a%20training%20session%20in%20a%20military%20airbase%20in%20Vasylkiv%20village%2C%20some%2030km%20of%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20Wednesday%2C%20November%2023%2C%202016.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d15805f5d4870019e39346%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGround%20staff%20directs%20a%20Mig-29%20fighter%20jet%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20after%20a%20flight%20during%20a%20training%20session%20at%20a%20military%20airbase%20in%20Vasylkiv%20village%2C%20some%2030km%20from%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20November%2023%2C%202016.%3Cp%3EDanil%20Shamkin%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20currently%20flying%20Soviet-made%20MiG-29%20and%20Su-27%20multirole%20fighters%20against%20a%20larger%20and%20technologically%20superior%20Russian%20air%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20are%20underdogs%20compared%20to%20Russian%20fighter%20aircraft%20like%20the%20MiG-31s%20and%20Su-25s%2C%20which%20feature%20advanced%20radars%20that%20allow%20them%20to%20see%20and%20locate%20targets%20further%20away%2C%20among%20other%20higher-end%20capabilities.%20The%20MiG-31%20in%20particular%20can%20track%20and%20engage%20multiple%20targets%20at%20once%2C%20and%20its%20fuel%20usage%20is%20more%20economical%20than%20the%20MiG-25%20from%20which%20it%20evolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Kyiv%20is%20also%20facing%20maintenance%20issues%20with%20its%20fighters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoing%20forward%2C%20maintaining%20them%20is%20going%20to%20get%20harder%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20access%20to%20factory%20parts%20manufactured%20in%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20Brynn%20Tannehill%2C%20a%20defense%20expert%20and%20former%20US%20Navy%20pilot%2C%20told%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20Ukraine%20will%20increasingly%20have%20to%20either%20machine%20their%20own%20parts%20or%20get%20them%20from%20NATO%20allies%20with%20Soviet-era%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20Ukraine's%20current%20aircraft%20don't%20also%20have%20their%20benefits.%20For%20one%2C%20Kyiv%20has%20experience%20operating%20these%20aircraft%2C%20but%20beyond%20that%2C%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3BMiG-29%20is%20actually%20significantly%20better%20at%20doing%20improvised%20field%20operations%26quot%3B%20than%20a%20jet%20like%20the%20F-16%2C%20she%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20rugged%20landing%20gear%20and%20protective%20air%20intake%20on%20the%20Soviet%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20been%20operating%20much%20of%20its%20air%20force%20from%20%26quot%3Bremote%20locations%2C%20places%20that%20the%20Russians%20wouldn't%20expect%2C%26quot%3B%20Tannehill%20added.%20F-16s%20would%20have%20trouble%20with%20that.%20%26quot%3BThe%20F-16%20were%20intended%20to%20operate%20off%20debris-free%2C%20very%20crystal%20smooth%20concrete%20runways.%20They%20were%20not%20designed%20to%20be%20on%20improvised%20fields%20or%20rough%20fields%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20advantages%20don't%20make%20up%20for%20the%20weaknesses%20the%20aircraft%20have%20in%20the%20face%20of%20Russian%20fighters%20and%2C%20importantly%2C%20Russian%20ground-based%20air%20defenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20for%20the%20Ukrainian%20air%20forces%20has%20been%20Russia's%20formidable%20air%20defenses%2C%20which%20have%20kept%20much%20of%20Kyiv's%20air%20force%20far%20from%20the%20front%20lines.%20The%20S-400%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%2C%20for%20example%2C%20give%20Moscow%20capabilities%20to%20eliminate%20a%20variety%20of%20targets%20out%20to%20a%20range%20of%20up%20to%20almost%20300%20miles.%C2%A0On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20armed%20with%20their%20own%20air%20defenses%20and%20Western%20systems%2C%20like%20US-made%20Patriots%2C%20have%20also%20been%20able%20to%20hamper%20Russian%20air%20operations%2C%20but%20greater%20combat%20capability%20is%20desired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUkraine%20has%20wanted%20F-16s%20since%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Russia's%20invasion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223519%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Air%20Force%20F-16%20Fighting%20Falcon%20aircraft%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63e5230896242f0019e826a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222341%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Air%20Force%20F-16%20Fighting%20Falcon%20aircraft%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Taylor%20Crul%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20long%20argued%20that%20F-16s%20with%20better%20radars%2C%20weapons%20capabilities%2C%20speed%2C%20and%20range%20will%20help%20it%20combat%20Russian%20threats%20and%20that%20they'd%20also%20be%20useful%20for%20Kyiv's%20air%20force%20in%20the%20long-term%2C%20potentially%20deterring%20Russia%20from%20engaging%20it%20in%20a%20future%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20May%2C%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20announced%20support%20for%20training%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20on%20F-16s%2C%20signaling%20plans%20for%20NATO%20to%20assist%20in%20the%20preparation%20and%20provision%20of%20fighter%20jets%20to%20Kyiv.%20US%20approval%20was%20initially%20a%20major%20roadblock%2C%20as%20concerns%20over%20Russian%20escalation%20have%20led%20the%20White%20House%20and%20Pentagon%20to%20at%20times%20hesitate%20on%20sending%20a%20variety%20of%20big-ticket%20items%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ff-16s-arent-ideal-ukraine-abrams-tanks-help-us-general-2023-7%5C%22%3EAbrams%20tank%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20if%20F-16s%2C%C2%A0which%20have%20their%20limitations%20against%20some%20of%20Russia's%20more%20modern%20aircraft%20and%20defenses%3Cstrong%3E%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20would%20kelp%20Kyiv's%20forces%20achieve%20%26quot%3Bair%20superiority%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20much%20of%20their%20usefulness%20would%20come%20down%20to%20what%20weapons%20are%20supplied.%20But%20the%20Western%20jets%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20give%20Ukraine%20better%20control%20over%20its%20airspace%20than%20its%20current%20fleet%20of%20MiG-29s%20and%20Su-27s%20as%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3EF-16s%20could%20quickly%20cover%20ground%20to%20help%20troops%20push%20the%20current%20battle%20lines%20while%20also%20providing%20support%20and%20firepower%20for%20offensive%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EF-16s%20are%20also%20more%20compatible%20with%20NATO%20system%20and%20weapons%20upgrades%2C%20Tannehill%20said.%20%26quot%3BDepending%20on%20what's%20supplied%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20it%20would%20allow%20the%20effective%20employment%20of%20a%20larger%20variety%20of%20NATO%20weapons%20systems.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20as%20Bronk%20explained%20to%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Ban%20F-16%20would%20potentially%20be%20more%20capable%20with%20the%20AGM-88%20high%20speed%20anti-radiation%20missile%20than%20the%20MiG-29%20and%20Su-27%2C%20which%20have%20been%20adapted%20to%20carry%20them%20for%20the%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20at%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%20The%20F-16%20would%20allow%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20to%20better%20and%20more%20easily%20detect%20and%20destroy%20enemy%20radars%20with%20the%20AGM-88%20HARM%2C%20whereas%20current%20Soviet%20fighters%20had%20to%20be%20irregularly%20modified%20to%20even%20carry%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20AGM-88%20missiles%2C%20other%20US%20weapons%20like%20the%20AIM-120%20Advanced%20Medium-Range%20Air-to-Air%20Missile%20(AMRAAM)%20or%20Joint%20Direct%20Attack%20Munition%20(JDAM)%2C%20both%20of%20which%20can%20be%20carried%20by%20certain%20F-16%20models%20could%20potentially%20deal%20damage%20to%20Russian%20air%20assets%20and%20ground%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EF-16s%20will%20help%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20a%20silver%20bullet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22F-16%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64962150c218ba0019a7f87d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EF-16%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%C2%A0while%20there%20are%20advantages%20to%20the%20F-16%2C%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20challenges%20to%20operating%20the%20jets.%20The%20logistical%20tail%20of%20the%20jets%20will%20be%20difficult%2C%20requiring%20a%20complete%20overhaul%20of%20where%20Ukraine%20gets%20parts%20from%20and%20how%20it%20conducts%20servicing%20and%20repairs.%20Pilots%20will%20need%20be%20trained%20on%20an%20entirely%20new%20system%2C%20something%20a%20US%20official%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fcoalition-aims-begin-ukrainian-f-16-pilot-training-by-summer-dutch-minister-2023-06-12%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIt%2520usually%2520takes%2520roughly%25202.5%2Cto%2520an%2520experienced%2520Ukrainian%2520pilot.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20take%20as%20little%20as%20four%20months%20with%20an%20experienced%20Ukrainian%20pilot%20but%20could%20potentially%20take%20significantly%20longer%20to%20fully%20master%20tactics%20and%20uses.%20It'll%20be%20expensive%20to%20operate%20F-16s%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20flip%20side%20to%20this%20is%20that%20they're%20very%20expensive%20to%20operate%20relative%20to%20the%20Soviet-era%20aircraft%20Ukraine%20is%20used%20to%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bthey%20would%20require%2C%20like%20any%20Western%20aircraft%2C%20a%20very%20different%20approach%20to%20maintenance%20servicing%20and%20general%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Bronk%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jets%20will%20Westernize%20Ukraine's%20way%20of%20war%2C%20but%20it%20will%20likely%20require%20a%20long-term%20relationship%20between%20Kyiv%20and%20NATO%20allies%20afterwards.%20That%20relationship%20could%20involve%C2%A0comba