%2F64d13a0ef5d4870019e35c1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222808%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20long%20line%20of%20job%20seekers%20are%20seen%20Tuesday%2C%20Oct.%2013%2C%202009%20at%20a%20career%20fair%20in%20Chicago.%3Cp%3E(AP%20Photo%2FKiichiro%20Sato)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20%242%20trillion%20corporate%20debt%20wall%20is%20about%20to%20shake%20the%20economy%20with%20job%20losses%2C%20according%20to%20Goldman%20Sachs.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bank%20estimated%20that%20the%20economy%20could%20shed%205%2C000%20jobs%20per%20month%20in%202024%20due%20to%20rising%20debt%20interest%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20will%20need%20to%20devote%20a%20greater%20share%20of%20their%20revenue%20to%20cover%20higher%20interest%20expense%20as%20they%20refinance%20their%20debt%20at%20higher%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman%20said.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20looming%20corporate%20debt%20wall%20of%20more%20than%20%242%20trillion%20is%20set%20to%20shake%20the%20economy%20over%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fgs-stock%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20said%20in%20a%20Sunday%20note%20that%20higher%20interest%20expenses%20tied%20to%20the%20refinancing%20of%20corporate%20debt%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20reduction%20in%20capital%20expenditures%20and%20a%20shedding%20of%20about%205%2C000%20jobs%20per%20month%20in%202024.%20That%20could%20double%20to%20a%20loss%20of%2010%2C000%20jobs%20per%20month%20in%202025%2C%20assuming%20interest%20rates%20remain%20elevated%20at%20their%20current%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20interest%20rates%20remain%20high%2C%20companies%20will%20need%20to%20devote%20a%20greater%20share%20of%20their%20revenue%20to%20cover%20higher%20interest%20expense%20as%20they%20refinance%20their%20debt%20at%20higher%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman%20Sachs'%20Jan%20Hatzius%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20find%20that%20for%20each%20additional%20dollar%20of%20interest%20expense%2C%20firms%20lower%20their%20capital%20expenditures%20by%2010%20cents%20and%20labor%20costs%20by%2020%20cents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20companies%20benefited%20immensely%20from%20the%20period%20of%20low%20interest%20rates%20before%202022.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fbac-stock%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%3EBank%20of%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Feconomy-outlook-us-recession-delayed-corporate-debt-binge-low-rates-2023-7%5C%22%3Edebt%20composition%20of%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies%20includes%20a%20whopping%2076%25%20in%20long-term%20fixed%20debt%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20much%20of%20which%20was%20secured%20at%20low%20single-digit%20rates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20interest%20rates%20stay%20elevated%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cuts-hikes-sticky-inflation-mortgage-home-prices-rent-2023-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Fed%2520has%2520hiked%2520interest%2Cevidence%2520that%2520inflation%2520is%2520easing.%5C%22%3Epotentially%20go%20higher%20as%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20continues%20to%20combat%20inflation%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20refinancing%20risks%20will%20grow%20more%20pronounced%2C%20especially%20over%20the%20next%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20estimates%20that%20corporate%20debt%20maturities%20will%20be%20%24230%20billion%20for%20the%20rest%20of%202023%2C%20%24790%20billion%20in%202024%2C%20and%20%241.07%20trillion%20in%202025%2C%20representing%20a%20combined%2016%25%20of%20all%20corporate%20debt.%20There's%20another%20%244%2B%20trillion%20in%20corporate%20debt%20set%20to%20mature%20from%202026%20through%202030%2C%20according%20to%20Goldman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20that%20wil