oreign%20policy%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20said%20that%20we%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20do%20anything%2C%20talks%20will%20not%20be%20successful%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20progress%2C%20disengagement%20cannot%20take%20place%2C%20but%20solutions%20were%20found%20in%20some%20of%20the%20focal%20points%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20as%20quoted%20by%20%3Cem%3EPTI%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20were%20five-six%20areas%20that%20were%20very%20tense%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20progress%20(there)%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Jaishankar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20May%202020%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20ongoing%20stand-off%20between%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20troops%20at%20multiple%20locations%20in%20Eastern%20Ladakh.%20Twenty%20Indian%20soldiers%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20first%20fatal%20encounter%20at%20the%20border%20in%20over%20four%20decades.%20Following%20several%20rounds%20of%20talks%2C%20there%20has%20been%20disengagement%20in%20around%20five%20points%2C%20which%20means%20that%20the%20two%20sides%20withdraw%20their%20troops%20from%20the%20stand-off%20point%20and%20also%20maintain%20a%20buffer%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20stalemate%20over%20the%20remaining%20friction%20points%20over%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok.%20Taking%20a%20completely%20opposite%20position%20from%20India%2C%20China%20has%20refused%20to%20budge%20on%20these%20two%20points%2C%20claiming%20that%20these%20are%20legacy%20issues%20of%20the%20larger%20boundary%20dispute%20and%20not%20related%20to%20the%20current%20stand-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Monday%20briefing%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20the%20negotiations%20were%20complex%20and%20both%20sides%20are%20engaged%20to%20find%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fon-china-jaishankar-says-dispute-is-over-forward-deployment-not-about-land-grab%5C%22%3EMEA%20organised%20press%20briefing%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jaishankar%20had%20claimed%20that%20the%20current%20border%20stand-off%20was%20not%20due%20to%20Chinese%20troops%20grabbing%20land%20from%20the%20Indian%20side%2C%20but%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cforward%20deployment%E2%80%9D%20of%20troops%20at%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control.%20The%20opposition%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Indian%20troops%20were%20unable%20to%20patrol%20areas%20due%20to%20this%20understanding%20which%20has%20meant%20that%20New%20Delhi%20is%20directly%20unable%20to%20control%20the%20territory%20that%20it%20did%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20after%202014%2C%20the%20Indian%20military%20and%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20are%20able%20to%20deploy%20and%20counter%20any%20Chinese%20movement%20better%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20%E2%80%9Cyes%2C%20absolutely%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Jaishankar%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20the%20overall%20mobility%20of%20both%20the%20armed%20forces%20and%20the%20civilian%20population%20in%20the%20border%20regions%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20He%20attributed%20this%20development%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20dedicated%20efforts%20in%20rapidly%20enhancing%20infrastructure%20in%20these%20frontier%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20he%20stated%20that%20ongoing%20infrastructure%20development%20along%20the%20India-China%20border%20will%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20shaping%20India%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20national%20security%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691430423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F13023738%2FScreenshot-2023-06-13-at-2.35.29-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fprogress-has-been-made-with-china-on-stand-off-areas-in-ladakh-says-jaishankar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The