80%94%20a%20major%20boon%20in%20cities%20simultaneously%20inflicted%20with%20housing%20crises%20and%20empty%20office%20towers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20found%20that%20about%2011%25%20of%20office%20buildings%20in%20the%20commercial%20centers%20of%20the%20105%20most%20populous%20US%20cities%20would%20be%20suitable%20for%20conversion%20to%20residential%20homes.%20Those%20%26quot%3Bzombie%26quot%3B%20properties%20%E2%80%94%20unrentable%20office%20buildings%20that%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzombie-office-buildings-are-sprouting-up-all-over-new-york-2023-7%5C%22%3Esitting%20empty%2C%20just%20accruing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20made%20into%20200-unit%20apartment%20buildings%20using%20conversion%20processes%20that%20would%20take%20less%20time%20than%20a%20new%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20residential%20conversions%2C%20the%20authors%20argue%2C%20would%20address%20the%20three%20major%20issues%20facing%20office%20buildings%20today%3A%20vacancies%20as%20a%20result%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20higher%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20climate%20regulations.%20The%20pandemic%20accelerated%20the%20rise%20of%20remote%20work%20and%20many%20businesses%20aren't%20renewing%20their%20office%20leases%2C%20leaving%20commercial%20buildings%20with%20high%20vacancy%20rates.%20Elevated%20interest%20rates%20mean%20it's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Frising-interest-rates-threaten-to-expose-office-buildings-inflated-values-11667213676%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharder%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20office%20real%20estate%20owners%20to%20pay%20back%20their%20mortgages.%20And%20new%20environmental%20regulations%20require%20that%20buildings%20meet%20certain%20energy%20efficiency%20standards%20that%20can%20require%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcitylimits.org%2F2023%2F02%2F21%2Foffice-buildings-could-evade-energy-upgrades-via-giant-loophole-in-nycs-climate-law-environmentalists-warn%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecostly%20renovations%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20severe%20housing%20supply%20crisis.%20To%20keep%20up%20with%20demand%2C%20the%20country%20needs%20to%20build%20an%20estimated%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Finsight%2F20210507-housing-supply%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3.8%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F03%2F08%2Fhomes%2Fhousing-shortage%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6.5%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20new%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20the%20Greater%20New%20York%20City%20region%C2%A0has%20the%20most%20buildings%20that%20fit%20their%20criteria%20for%20residential%20conversion.%20The%20San%20Francisco%C2%A0and%20Los%20Angeles%C2%A0metro%20areas%20were%20the%20runners-up.%20All%20three%20metropolitan%20areas%20have%20among%20the%20highest%20housing%20costs%20in%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurning%20office%20buildings%20into%20apartments%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgothamist.com%2Fnews%2Fthe-countrys-biggest-office-to-apartment-conversion-is-underway-inside-the-old-daily-news-office%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisn't%20a%20new%20concept%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it's%20one%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Foffice-of-the-mayor%2Fnews%2F022-23%2Fmayor-adams-recommendations-convert-underused-offices-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20City%20has%20embraced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20theory.%20However%2C%20as%20Insider's%20Jordan%20Hart%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturning-zombie-offices-into-apartments-tricky-and-expensive-2023-7%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20can%20be%20both%20difficult%20and%20expensive%20to%20convert%20buildings%20amidst%20tight%20zoning%20regulations%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F01%2Fupshot%2Famerican-cities-office-conversion.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20pushback%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20high%20conversion%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20researchers%20specifically%20focused%20on%20little-used%20downtown%20buildings%20that%20were%20built%20before%201990%20without%20sprawling%20square%20footage%20across%20the%20floors.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F03%2F11%2Fupshot%2Foffice-conversions.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOlder%20buildings%3C%2Fa%3E%20tend%20to%20have%20smaller%20floor%20plans%20that%20allow%20more%20light%20into%20the%20interior%20without%20requiring%20a%20light%20shaft%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuildings%20contribute%20almost%2030%25%20of%20the%20US's%20total%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions.%20The%20study%20found%20that%2072%25%20of%20large%20office%20buildings%20in%20New%20York%20City%20emit%20more%20climate-warming%20gasses%20than%20permitted%20under%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2021%2F04%2F22%2Ffact-sheet-president-biden-sets-2030-greenhouse-gas-pollution-reduction-target-aimed-at-creating-good-paying-union-jobs-and-securing-u-s-leadership-on-clean-energy-technologies%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20country's%202030%20emissions%20goals%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20process%20of%20converting%20office%20spaces%20to%20homes%2C%20developers%20could%20retrofit%20the%20buildings%20to%20meet%20new%20energy%20efficiency%20standards.%20Eco-friendly%20conversions%20of%20those%20buildings%20could%20be%20bolstered%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-inflation-reduction-act-means-finances-tax-health-climate-democrats-2022-8%5C%22%3EInflation%20Reduction%20Act's%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20tax%20credits%3C%2Fa%3E%20meant%20to%20incentivize%20green%20technology%20and%20building%2C%20with%20the%20researchers%20finding%20that%20office%20conversions%20could%20potentially%20qualify%20for%20over%20%2410%20billion%20in%20grants.%20It's%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F07%2F24%2F1189403058%2Fdowntown-real-estate-housing-offices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreener%20to%20renovate%3C%2Fa%3E%20existing%20buildings%20than%20constructing%20new%20ones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20office%20buildings%20require%20some%20retrofitting%20to%20be%20turned%20from%20sprawling%20workplaces%20to%20livable%20apartments.%20For%20instance%2C%20New%20York%20City%20%E2%80%94%20among%20other%20areas%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0mandate%20that%20bedrooms%20have%20to%20have%20windows.%20While%20that's%20likely%20more%20pleasant%20for%20renters%2C%20it%20may%20prove%20to%20be%20burdensome%20in%20office%20conversions%3B%20it%20would%20require%20a%20ring%20of%20bedrooms%20around%20the%20office%20building's%20walls%2C%20leaving%20what%20the%20researchers%20say%20is%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%20dead%20space%20in%20the%20center.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20for%20renters%20who%20like%20their%20windows%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20legally%20required%20to%20have%20them%20%E2%80%94%20the%20researchers%20posit%20that%20those%20wide%20empty%20spaces%20in%20the%20center%20could%20be%20used%20for%20common%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20only%20solution%20needed%20to%20address%20an%20ever-worsening%20housing%20crisis.%20But%2C%20as%20the%20researchers%20conclude%2C%20%26quot%3BWhile%20challenges%20abound%2C%20the%20potential%20to%20reimagine%20urban%20spaces%20for%20an%20economically%20and%20ecologically%20more%20sustainable%20future%20is%20immense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWould%20you