20the%20administration's%20authority%2C%20and%20they%20want%20the%20court%20to%20block%20it%20from%20being%20carried%20out.%20The%20Education%20Department%20pushed%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Biden-Harris%20Administration%20is%20fighting%20every%20day%20to%20fix%20the%20broken%20student%20loan%20system%20and%20make%20sure%20borrowers%20get%20the%20relief%20they%20earned%2C%20need%2C%20and%20deserve%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20department%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BThis%20lawsuit%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20desperate%20attempt%20from%20right%20wing%20special%20interests%20to%20keep%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20borrowers%20in%20debt%2C%20even%20though%20these%20borrowers%20have%20earned%20the%20forgiveness%20that%20is%20promised%20through%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans.%20%C2%A0We%20are%20not%20going%20to%20back%20down%20or%20give%20an%20inch%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20defending%20working%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-idr-account-adjustment-2023-7%5C%22%3Ealready%20started%20notifying%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20qualify%20to%20have%20their%20loans%20forgiven%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%2C%20writing%20in%20its%20email%20to%20borrowers%20that%20%26quot%3Byou%20are%20now%20eligible%20to%20have%20some%20or%20all%20of%20your%20student%20loans%20forgiven%20because%20you%20have%20reached%20the%20necessary%20240-%20or%20300-months'%20of%20payments%20under%20IDR.%26quot%3B%20Should%20this%20lawsuit%20progress%2C%20it%20risks%20throwing%20that%20relief%20off%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20in%20the%20latest%20lawsuit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20lawsuit%20against%20student-debt%20relief%20for%20the%20New%20Civil%20Liberties%20Alliance.%20Back%20in%20October%2C%20it%20represented%20the%20Cato%20Institute%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-suing-biden-student-loan-forgiveness-koch-backed-cato-institute-2022-10%5C%22%3Efiling%20a%20lawsuit%20to%20block%20Biden's%20broad%20plan%20to%20cancel%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%20in%20student%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20federal%20borrowers%2C%20which%20ended%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-supreme-court-strikes-down-debt-cancellation-2023-5%5C%22%3Egetting%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20end%20of%20June%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20different%20lawsuit%20that%20also%20challenged%20the%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20similarities%20in%20the%20arguments%20from%20the%20October%20lawsuit%2C%20and%20the%20most%20recent%20one%20challenging%20the%20income-driven%20repayment%20relief.%20Both%20complaints%20referenced%20the%20impact%20the%20relief%20would%20have%20on%20recruiting%20incentives%20through%20the%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%20program%2C%20which%20forgives%20student%20debt%20for%20government%20and%20nonprofit%20workers%20after%20ten%20years%20of%20qualifying%20payments.%20With%20the%20Cato%20Institute%20and%20Mackinac%20Center%20being%20nonprofits%2C%20the%20complaint%20said%20that%20PSLF%20%26quot%3Bmaterially%20helps%20qualifying%20employers%20attract%20and%20retain%20borrower-employees%20who%20might%20otherwise%20choose%20higher-paying%20employment%20with%20nonqualifying%20employers%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlawful%20cancellation%20of%20student-loan%20debt%20reduces%20the%20amount%20of%20a%20borrower's%20PSLF-cancellable%20debt%20and%20thus%20reduces%20the%20amount%20by%20which%20PSLF%20benefits%20qualified%20employment%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20claimed%20that%20Biden's%20relief%20violated%20the%20Administrative%20Procedures%20Act%20and%20did%20not%20solicit%20necessary%20public%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20however%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20in%20January%20published%20its%20proposed%20rule%20on%20reforming%20income-driven%20repayment%20on%20the%20Federal%20Register%2C%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20negotiated%20rulemaking%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20this%20lawsuit%20will%20impact%20debt%20discharges%2C%20but%20the%20administration%20has%20made%20no%20indication%20yet%20that%20the%20process%20will%20be%20halted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-latest-lawsuit-block-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691427422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F645b9c6a65a21600192fe895%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-latest-lawsuit-block-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Conservative%20groups%20recently%20sued%20Biden%20over%20his%20latest%20effort%20to%20cancel%20%2439%20billion%20in%20student%20debt%20for%20over%20800%2C000%20student-loan%20borrowers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-latest-lawsuit-block-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LIVE%3A%20PM%20does%20not%20obey%20SC%2C%20Kejriwal%20after%20RS%20passes%20Delhi%20services%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691427363000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F07%2Ffull%2F1691426458-8516.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fdaily-breaking-news-latest-updates-today-live-7-august-2023-delhi-service-bill-article-370-removal-123080700076_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Catch%20all%20the%20latest%20news%20updates%20live%20from%20across%20the%20glo