d%20are%20denied%20bail%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2022%2F10%2F19%2Fforgetting-the-basics-the-bail-orders-in-jyoti-jagtap-and-umar-khalids-cases%2F%5C%22%3Eothers%20get%20it%20for%20the%20same%20offence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20there%20is%20no%20admission%20of%20how%20the%20mainstream%20has%20excluded%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20Muslim%20like%20Umar%20Khalid%20crosses%20boundaries%2C%20there%20is%20a%20further%20panic%20attack.%20A%20young%20articulate%20Muslim%20man%20who%20does%20not%20wear%20a%20skull%20cap%2C%20who%20is%20an%20atheist%2C%20who%20did%20his%20Ph.D.%20from%20JNU%20in%20history%20on%20Adivasis%20in%20Singbhum%20is%20seen%20as%20an%20anomaly%20in%20the%20segregated%20world%20the%20RSS%20wants%20to%20create.%20The%20attempt%20is%20then%20to%20reduce%20him%20to%20just%20one%20aspect%20of%20his%20identity%20%E2%80%93%20so%20that%20whatever%20else%20he%20does%20or%20says%20or%20writes%20in%20the%20end%20he%20must%20be%20seen%20merely%20as%20a%20Muslim%2C%20and%20by%20extension%2C%20violent%2C%20anti-national%2C%20and%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20mainstream%E2%80%9D.%20So%20dangerous%20that%20he%20has%20been%20in%20jail%20for%20three%20years%20without%20bail.%20It%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20so%20many%20of%20the%20young%20people%20who%20were%20arrested%20for%20the%20anti-CAA%20protests%20were%20Muslim%20students%20at%20India%E2%80%99s%20leading%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20number%20of%20people%20have%20written%20about%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farticle-14.com%2Fpost%2F1000-days-without-trial-or-bail-for-umar-khalid-denied-bail-despite-false-allegations-fabrications-and-inconsistencies-6482500d54eea%5C%22%3Eflimsy%20the%20legal%20case%20against%20Umar%3C%2Fa%3E%20is.%20Among%20other%20absurdities%2C%20he%20is%20charged%20with%20being%20on%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20and%20for%20using%20phrases%20like%20%3Cem%3Einquilabi%20salaam%3C%2Fem%3E%20(revolutionary%20greetings).%20It%20is%20pure%20judicial%20bigotry%20to%20call%20his%20speech%20%E2%80%98obnoxious%E2%80%99%20when%20he%20is%20talking%20of%20pitting%20love%20against%20hate%2C%20even%20as%20the%20obnoxious%20Kapil%20Mishra%20or%20Anurag%20Thakur%2C%20whose%20hate%20speeches%20served%20as%20a%20spark%20for%20the%20attack%20on%20Muslims%20in%20Delhi%202020%2C%20roam%20free%20and%20prosper%20with%20official%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20want%2C%20instead%2C%20to%20focus%20on%20Umar%20the%20historian%2C%20and%20the%20loss%20to%20the%20academic%20world%20by%20locking%20up%20this%20brilliant%20mind.%20As%20someone%20who%20has%20worked%20extensively%20on%20Adivasi%20history%2C%20I%20truly%20felt%20that%20I%20was%20learning%20something%20new%20when%20I%20read%20his%20thesis.%20And%20when%20one%20considers%20that%20the%20thesis%20was%20written%20while%20the%20student%20was%20still%20under%20trial%20for%20sedition%2C%20had%20already%20spent%20time%20in%20jail%2C%20had%20been%20fired%20upon%20and%20narrowly%20survived%2C%20and%20had%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20such%20mass%20media%20defamation%20and%20hysteria%20that%20he%20could%20not%20travel%20freely%2C%20it%20is%20not%20only%20brilliant%20but%20heroic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20had%20been%20rusticated%20in%20his%20last%20semester%20of%20thesis%20writing%20when%20one%20needs%20the%20university%20the%20most%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F887922%2Fdelhi-high-court-asks-jnu-to-accept-theses-from-five-students-penalised-over-sedition-row%5C%22%3Ehad%20to%20go%20to%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20order%20to%20be%20allowed%20to%20submit%20the%20thesis.%20It%20is%20ironic%20that%20the%20same%20judge%20who%20enabled%20him%20and%20others%20to%20submit%20their%20theses%20at%20JNU%20later%20denied%20him%20bail.%20Surely%2C%20he%20knew%20the%20odds%20this%20young%20man%20had%20faced%2C%20obstacles%20that%20would%20have%20ground%20down%20any%20lesser%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUmar%20could%20have%20chosen%20to%20lie%20low%2C%20and%20like%20other%20recent%20PhDs%2C%20busy%20himself%20in%20applying%20for%20post%20docs%20or%20jobs%2C%20or%2C%20as%20those%20who%20want%20to%20get%20ahead%20in%20the%20current%20system%20do%2C%20publish%20in%20predatory%20journals.%20But%20he%20chose%20the%20hard%20way%2C%20putting%20his%20heart%20and%20soul%20into%20the%20struggle%20for%20universal%20citizenship%2C%20against%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20and%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20the%20usual%20assumption%2C%20the%20CAA%20would%20have%20disenfranchised%20not%20just%20Muslims%2C%20but%20women%2C%20Adivasis%2C%20Dalits%2C%20the%20poor%20more%20generally%20%E2%80%93%20all%20those%20who%20do%20not%20have%20records%20or%20written%20genealogies.%20But%20his%20only%20reward%20for%20this%20extraordinary%20selflessness%20in%20attempting%20to%20uphold%20Indian%20democracy%20has%20been%20a%20jail%20term%2C%20which%20has%20already%20stretched%20for%20three%20endless%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUmar%2C%20the%20historian%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUmar%E2%80%99s%20thesis%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Contesting%20Claims%20and%20Contingencies%20of%20Rule%3A%20Singhbhum%201800%20%E2%80%93%202000%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20a%20well-researched%20and%20deeply%20insightful%20exploration%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20Adivasis%20and%20the%20state%2C%20in%20what%20is%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20%E2%80%98isolated%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98backward%E2%80%99%20tracts%20of%20India%2C%20even%20as%20it%20is%20the%20site%20of%20extensive%20mining.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUmar%20argues%20that%20contrary%20to%20the%20received%20wisdom%20which%20has%20pitted%20a%20homogenous%20Adivasi%20society%20against%20the%20state%2C%20the%20state%20intervened%20through%20the%20fractures%20within%20Adivasi%20society.%20The%20colonial%20policy%20of%20indirect%20rule%20helped%20to%20strengthen%20a%20particular%20class%20within%20the%20Ho%20community.%20Existing%20hierarchies%20were%20strengthened%20and%20new%20ones%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20thesis%20looks%20in%20detail%20at%20the%20creation%20of%20Singbhum%20as%20a%20region%20and%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20Manki-Munda%20(local%20headmen)%20system%20was%20co-opted%20into%20colonial%20governance%20structures.%20He%20analyses%20how%20this%20system%20helped%20in%20extending%20arable%20land%2C%20raising%20rents%2C%20and%20managing%20the%20forests.%20He%20then%20places%20Jaipal%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20Adivasi%20Mahasabha%20within%20this%20longer%20history%2C%20showing%20how%20it%20drew%20on%20colonial%20ideas%20of%20exceptionalism%20and%20Adivasi%20difference%20to%20negotiate%20a%20position%20of%20autonomy%2C%20albeit%20limited%2C%20within%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20in%20the%20thesis%20shows%20the%20mark%20of%20someone%20who%20desires%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20bloody%20revolution.%20Everything%20in%20this%20thesis%20shows%20someone%20who%20is%20engaging%20deeply%20with%20democracy%20and%20its%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUmar%20has%20put%20this%20jail%20term%20to%20productive%20use%20by%20reading%20extensively.%20In%20between%2C%20he%20also%20managed%20to%20write%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-peoples-historian-ranajit-guha-one-of-the-most-magnificent-historians-of-modern-india%2Fcid%2F1936712%5C%22%3Eobituary%20of%20Ranajit%20Guha%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Speaking%20purely%20as%20an%20academic%2C%20this%20young%20man%20needs%20to%20be%20out%20of%20jail%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20to%20live%20a%20normal%20life%20and%20eventually%20find%20the%20time%20to%20publish%20his%20thesis%20as%20a%20book.%20The%20last%20para%20of%20his%20thesis%20ends%20on%20a%20poignant%20note%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CI%20specifically%20wanted%20to%20look%20at%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20those%20at%20the%20very%