business%2C%20Harsha%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CSince%20it%20is%20a%20very%20unique%20concept%2C%20it%20took%20us%20six%20months%20to%20understand%20the%20market%20and%20gain%20the%20doctors%E2%80%99%20trust.%20Given%20my%20age%2C%20they%20were%20doubtful%20if%20I%20would%20be%20able%20to%20manage%20the%20network.%20At%20first%2C%20managing%20the%20kitchen%20and%20chefs%20was%20a%20little%20challenging%2C%20but%20with%20experience%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20do%20better.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESri%20Harsha%20started%20the%20company%20with%20an%20initial%20investment%20of%20Rs%2015%20lakh.%20Today%2C%20the%20company%20generates%20a%20monthly%20revenue%20of%20Rs%207%20lakh.%20He%20aims%20to%20expand%20the%20services%20to%20Bengaluru%20by%20the%20year-end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20vision%20is%20to%20provide%20end-to-end%20medical%20nutrition%20therapy%20to%20patients%20and%20promote%20general%20wellness%20for%20health-conscious%20people.%20I%20once%20needed%20such%20a%20service%20myself%2C%20and%20now%20we%20are%20witnessing%20how%20our%20nutrition%20support%20helps%20patients%20with%20diabetes%20manage%20their%20blood%20glucose%20levels%2C%20and%20malnourished%20children%20thrive%20and%20gain%20weight.%20This%20kind%20of%20positive%20impact%20keeps%20us%20motivated%20to%20expand%20our%20work%20further%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sri%20Harsha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20%3Cem%3EAll%20photos%3A%20Sri%20Harsha.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691412754000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fhypothallamus-1-1691411037.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D326524%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sri%20Harsha%2C%20along%20with%20Sharath%20Chandra%20and%20Nirali%20Parikh%2C%20co-founded%20%E2%80%98Hypothalamus%E2%80%99%20to%20address%20the%20healthcare%20gap%20in%20the%20food%20industry.%20They%20provide%20health-focused%20meal%20delivery%20service%20for%20patients%20with%20cancer%2C%20diabetes%2C%20PCOS%2C%20etc.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F326524%2Ffood-for-patiets-of-diabetes-cancer-pcos-home-delivery-hypothalamus-mumbai%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google%20Offers%20Rebate%20At%20Campus%20Hotel%20In%20US%20To%20Lure%20Staff%20Back%20To%20Office%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWork%20From%20Home%20became%20a%20worldwide%20norm%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Now%20that%20Covid-19%20no%20longer%20qualifies%20as%20a%20global%20emergency%2C%20companies%20are%20asking%20their%20staff%20to%20return%20to%20the%20workplace%20on%20a%20full-time%20basis.%20However%2C%20not%20everyone%20is%20comfortable%20with%20the%20idea.%20In%20an%20effort%20to%C2%A0lure%20its%20employees%20back%20to%20the%20office%2C%20Google%20is%20offering%20its%20workers%20discounted%20nightly%20stays%20at%20a%20hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20giant%20is%20now%20offering%20a%20%26quot%3BSummer%20Special%26quot%3B%20program%20to%20let%20employees%20stay%20at%20an%20on-campus%20hotel%20for%20a%20discount%2C%20around%20%2499%20per%20day%20(around%20Rs%208%2C190)%2C%C2%A0according%20to%20materials%20viewed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fgoogle-offers-on-campus-hotel-special-to-lure-workers-back-in.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNBC%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%20description%20states%20that%20the%20special%20will%20run%20through%20September%2030%20in%20hopes%20it'll%20''make%20it%20easier%20for%20Googlers%20to%20transition%20to%20the%20hybrid%20workplace.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discounted%20hotel%20rate%20only%20lasts%20until%20September%2030th%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20much%20it%20will%20cost%20after%20that.%20Notably%2C%20the%20hotel%20is%20owned%20by%20the%20online%20search%20giant%20and%20is%20housed%20on%20its%