ction%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2014%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fsmartphone-market-to-shrink-again-this-year-11691349442808.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20smartphone%20shipments%20crossed%20100%20million%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202015%2C%20peaked%20at%20160%20million%20in%202021%2C%20and%20fell%2010%25%20to%20144%20million%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20IDC%2C%20shipments%20may%20fall%20a%20further%202-6%25%20to%20touch%20135-140%20million%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20high%20inflationary%20conditions%20have%20squeezed%20disposable%20incomes%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20pyramid%2C%20which%20have%20impacted%20upgrades%20and%20new%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUsers%20are%20upgrading%20or%20changing%20devices%20after%2036%20months%20or%20more%2C%20which%20used%20to%20be%2018%20months%20to%20two%20years%20till%20some%20time%20ago.%20The%20replacement%20cycles%20are%20getting%20longer%2C%20which%20is%20bound%20to%20impact%20smartphone%20players%20and%20the%20overall%20market%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20executive%20told%20the%20business%20daily%2C%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20slow%20demand%20and%20inventory%20build-up%2C%20which%20was%20carried%20forward%20from%202022%2C%20is%20leading%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20smartphone%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShilpi%20Jain%2C%20senior%20research%20analyst%20at%20Counterpoint%20Research%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EMint%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20decline%20is%20due%20to%20slow%20demand%20and%20inventory%20build-up%2C%20which%20was%20carried%20from%202022.%20Most%20of%20the%20brands%20focussed%20on%20clearing%20existing%20inventory%20in%20Q1%20and%20Q2%202023%20so%20that%20they%20can%20plan%20to%20push%20new%20launches%E2%80%99%20inventory%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year%20during%20the%20festive%20season.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJain%20expects%20the%20smartphone%20market%20to%20contract%20by%201%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findias-smartphone-market-budget-phones-economy%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Smartphone%20Market%20Remains%20Under%20Pressure%20on%20Weak%20Demand%20for%20Budget%20Phones%3A%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20top%20executive%20at%20a%20telecom%20firm%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20users%20are%20holding%20on%20to%20their%20devices%20much%20longer%20than%20earlier.%20This%2C%20the%20executive%20said%2C%20is%20because%20better%20quality%20phones%20are%20available%20at%20affordable%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20vendors%20and%20manufacturers%20are%20working%20to%20ensure%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20over-supply%20products%2C%20and%20offer%20discounts%20during%20the%20festive%20period%20which%20starts%20around%20Diwali.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmartphone%20sales%20are%20an%20important%20indicator%20of%20private%20consumption%2C%20which%20is%20the%20biggest%20component%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20private%20consumption%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ftop-20-driving-gdp-growth-the-rest-are-travelling-steerage%5C%22%3Ehas%20grown%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%20by%20a%20measly%202.8%25%20at%20constant%20prices%20in%20Q4%2C%20although%20the%20GDP%20growth%20for%20January%20to%20March%202022-23%20surprised%20on%20the%20upside%20at%206.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPronab%20Sen%2C%20former%20chief%20statistician%20of%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ftop-20-driving-gdp-growth-the-rest-are-travelling-steerage%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20M.K.%20Venu%20that%20though%20GDP%20numbers%20show%20some%20signs%20of%20recovery%2C%20a%20very%20skewed%20income%20distribution%20is%20also%20visible%2C%20and%20is%20most%20